com.karmant.syn

Class TerminalNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.karmant.syn.SynNode
      • com.karmant.syn.TerminalNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ValueNode

    public abstract class TerminalNode
extends SynNode
    Terminal node - a node that does not contain child nodes. Produced by terminal grammar symbols and constants. Has two direct subclasses: TokenNode and ValueNode.

    • Method Detail

      • getTokenDescriptor

        public abstract TokenDescriptor getTokenDescriptor()
        Returns the corresponding token descriptor.
        • If this node was produced by a terminal grammar symbol, the token descriptor of that symbol is returned.
        • If the node was produced by a constant of integer, floating-point or string type, the descriptor of the corresponding literal token is returned (e. g. TokenDescriptor.INTEGER).
        • Otherwise, null is returned.
        Returns:
        the token descriptor.

      • getString

        public abstract java.lang.String getString()
        If this token node was produced by a custom keyword or a key-character symbol, the literal of that symbol is returned. Otherwise, the return value is the same as for ValueNode.getString().
        Returns:
        the string value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this node is a value and its type is not a string.

        public final TextPos getPos()
